title: Corbio
description: Corbio was an ancient city of Latium located on the northeastern flank of the Alban Hills, although its precise location is no longer secure. This Latin city is said to have fallen to the Aequi and then been the subject of contention between the Aequi and the Romans, ultimately recaptured by the latter after Cincinnatus' victory at Mons Algidus in 458 B.C.

properties.description: Rocca Priora, Lazio, is a possible location of ancient Corbio in Latium. Coordinates after GeoHack.
